00:17.522 --> 00:19.589
No! No! No! No!

00:20.792 --> 00:22.525
Daddy, I want to go home!

00:25.464 --> 00:27.430
No! No!

00:28.533 --> 00:30.900
Here's Daddy. Here's Daddy.

00:30.902 --> 00:32.168
It's just a bad dream,
sweetheart.

00:32.170 --> 00:33.603
It's just a bad dream.

00:33.605 --> 00:35.738
I got you.

00:35.740 --> 00:38.241
I got you.

00:38.243 --> 00:40.777
I got you.
I got you, sweetie.

00:40.779 --> 00:43.446
It's gonna be all right.
It's all right.

01:01.099 --> 01:04.566
Been a few weeks now
since the last one.

01:04.569 --> 01:06.436
Beginning to think maybe
she's ready to get past it,

01:06.438 --> 01:09.239
but last night,
man, it just...

01:11.676 --> 01:13.877
It was awful.

01:13.879 --> 01:15.945
Another nightmare, huh?

01:15.947 --> 01:17.647
Yeah.

01:18.450 --> 01:21.518
The whole thing--
the abduction...

01:21.520 --> 01:24.521
and being locked
up in a cage...

01:24.523 --> 01:27.357
and watching
Ian die and...

01:27.359 --> 01:30.293
It just plays over and over
on a loop in her head.

01:30.295 --> 01:33.263
And she can't...
It just never ends.

01:33.265 --> 01:36.099
That son of a
bitch Ian, man.

01:36.101 --> 01:38.034
He really got
under my daughter's skin.

01:38.036 --> 01:39.903
She can't shake it.

01:39.905 --> 01:43.373
Yeah.

01:43.375 --> 01:47.176
We both know what it's like
not to want to close your eyes.

01:51.750 --> 01:54.918
Only cure for that though
is time.

01:54.920 --> 01:58.087
This is killing me.

02:00.292 --> 02:02.725
I feel utterly helpless.

02:02.727 --> 02:05.628
Every night, I pray to God
to take this thing off of her

02:05.630 --> 02:07.764
and put it on me
'cause I can handle it.

02:07.766 --> 02:09.164
This is my little girl.

02:14.039 --> 02:16.573
She shouldn't
have to carry this.

02:19.678 --> 02:21.210
You know what though, Lou?

02:21.212 --> 02:23.580
Let me tell you something.

02:23.582 --> 02:26.883
You're doing
the only thing you can do.

02:26.885 --> 02:28.685
You're being there
for Samantha.

02:28.687 --> 02:30.620
Knowing she's got
a father that loves her

02:30.622 --> 02:34.223
and will do whatever it takes
to keep her safe...

02:34.225 --> 02:35.391
that's exactly

02:35.393 --> 02:37.427
what she needs right now.

02:48.273 --> 02:49.806
<i>Fool!</i>

02:49.808 --> 02:51.841
<i>You've fallen</i>
<i>right into my trap!</i>

02:51.843 --> 02:53.009
<i>Without you to protect them,</i>

02:53.011 --> 02:55.678
the people of Earth
will perish!

02:55.680 --> 02:58.081
You better get in there
and help save Gotham.

02:58.083 --> 03:00.149
Carpool's gonna be here
in ten minutes.

03:00.151 --> 03:03.720
All right, you two warriors!
Let me see this!

03:04.923 --> 03:06.956
Let's go, Supermen.

03:08.026 --> 03:09.892
To school!

03:09.894 --> 03:11.828
Capes down,
brush your teeth,

03:11.830 --> 03:14.464
grab your backpacks.

03:14.466 --> 03:17.166
I really appreciate you
rearranging your day like this.

03:17.168 --> 03:19.035
I know it's a pain.
Hey.

03:19.037 --> 03:20.837
Comes with the territory
when you are married

03:20.839 --> 03:22.472
to a real superhero.

03:22.474 --> 03:24.707
I'll make it up to you tonight.

03:24.709 --> 03:26.175
Mm.
I promise.

03:26.177 --> 03:28.177
You always do.

03:28.179 --> 03:29.545
I...
Not negotiable.

03:29.547 --> 03:32.415
You have a long day
of surgery ahead.

03:32.417 --> 03:33.983
Love you.

03:33.985 --> 03:35.818
I love you, too.

03:35.820 --> 03:39.455
I wish you could babysit
me every day, Poppy.

03:39.457 --> 03:42.725
I wish I could, too, kiddo.

03:42.727 --> 03:44.327
Are you gonna be here
after school?

03:44.329 --> 03:46.829
Oh, you better
believe it.

03:46.831 --> 03:50.366
Um, your parents
get home

03:50.368 --> 03:53.236
around dinner time, eh?

03:53.238 --> 03:57.440
What do you say we take them
to J.J. Dolan's for some pizza?

03:57.442 --> 03:59.142
Cool.

03:59.144 --> 04:01.611
We're gonna
have fun, Poppy.

04:01.613 --> 04:03.379
We sure will.

04:03.381 --> 04:06.315
Be a good boy.

04:06.317 --> 04:09.085
You, too.

04:21.099 --> 04:23.433
- Is the patient prepped?
- Yes.

04:23.435 --> 04:25.635
Okay, go ahead and place
an A line and a central line

04:25.637 --> 04:27.770
before he goes into the O.R.
Do you want me to call a...?

04:27.772 --> 04:29.572
Yes, and then we can put
the ventricular drain

04:29.574 --> 04:30.973
to stabilize
the intracranial bleeding.

04:30.975 --> 04:32.208
How far out are you?

04:32.210 --> 04:33.242
I'll be up in a minute.

04:33.244 --> 04:34.811
I'm pulling into the garage now.

04:46.858 --> 04:50.460
<i>(Hawaii Five-O</i>
theme song plays)

04:50.484 --> 04:54.484
<font color="#00FF00">♪ Hawaii Five-O 5x12 ♪</font>
<font color="#00FFFF">Poina 'ole</font>
